<subSubSection id="C361651AFFB2B342FF6B4881FB34FDF6" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC43691FFB2B342FF6B4881FB34FDF6" blockId="80.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FFB2B342FF6B4881FEEAFE1A" bold="true" box="[199,315,441,465]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FFB2B342FEED4882FE32FE1A" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[321,483,441,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wilsoni">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FFB2B342FEED4882FE32FE1A" box="[321,483,441,465]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Igerna wilsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FFB2B342FD794881FCB8FE1A" box="[725,873,441,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FFB2B342FD794881FCB8FE1A" box="[725,873,441,465]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Japanagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but lacks the cross veins between the claval veins. It shares a ventral process of the aedeagus with some undescribed species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FFB2B342FBA948E6FB81FE3E" authorityName="Kirkaldy. It" authorityYear="1903" box="[1029,1104,478,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FFB2B342FBA948E6FB81FE3E" box="[1029,1104,478,501]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Igerna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Afrotropical region and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FFB2B342FF6B4B3AFEEDFDD2" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[199,316,513,537]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinlani">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FFB2B342FF6B4B3AFEEDFDD2" box="[199,316,513,537]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">I. quinlani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. None of the other 
<collectingRegion id="49BFF873FFB2B342FDB74B39FDA6FDD2" box="[539,631,513,537]" country="Oman" name="Shamal ash Sharqiyah" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Oriental</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FFB2B342FDD34B3AFD1BFDD2" authorityName="Kirkaldy. It" authorityYear="1903" box="[639,714,514,537]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FFB2B342FDD34B3AFD1BFDD2" box="[639,714,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Igerna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses a spine-like structure on the aedeagus. The species is named after Dr M. R. Wilson, in recognition of his contributions to Auchenorrhyncha systematics.
</paragraph>
